docs.abstract: For many, it’s a chance to kick back at beaches and barbecues. But for others, it’s a mark of the country’s shameful treatment of Indigenous people: Invasion Day.
docs.snippet: For many, it’s a chance to kick back at beaches and barbecues. But for others, it’s a mark of the country’s shameful treatment of Indigenous people: Invasion Day.
docs.lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE, Australia — Those who celebrate Australia Day, the country’s national holiday, associate it with barbecues and pool parties. But for those who protest against it, it is a reminder of the continent’s brutal colonization.

headline.main: Day of Celebration or Mourning? Australia Grapples With Its National Holiday
headline.print_headline: Australia’s National Holiday  Brings Celebration for Some  But Resentment for Others

docs.abstract: The defense from Trump supporters arrested in the Capitol assault is emerging in court papers and interviews — and could play a role in impeachment proceedings.
docs.snippet: The defense from Trump supporters arrested in the Capitol assault is emerging in court papers and interviews — and could play a role in impeachment proceedings.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the two weeks since a raging mob stormed the Capitol, President Trump has shown no sign that he believes he shares responsibility for the worst incursion on the halls of Congress in more than two centuries. Shielding him further, his loyalists have started shifting blame for the attack to an array of distracting bogeymen: far-left anti-fascists, Black Lives Matter activists, even vague conspiracies of a setup involving Vice President Mike Pence.

headline.main: ‘I Answered the Call of My President’: Rioters Say Trump Urged Them On
headline.print_headline: We Just Followed Trump’s Cue, Several Accused in Rioting Say

docs.snippet: Advice from therapists, religious leaders and people who suffered terrible wrongs on ways to find repentance and resolution.
docs.lead_paragraph: Despite President-elect Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s plea to let our “better angels prevail” and the comedian Dave Chappelle’s “Saturday Night Live” monologue where he told Americans, “We have to forgive each other,” reconciliation and forgiveness can be a long, difficult process. headline.main: How to Get Someone to Apologize

docs.abstract: A Massachusetts teenager had been at odds with her mother over politics for years. Now their feud is a Twitter sensation.
docs.snippet: A Massachusetts teenager had been at odds with her mother over politics for years. Now their feud is a Twitter sensation.
docs.lead_paragraph: For four years, Helena Duke, an 18-year-old high school senior in Massachusetts, had been growing further apart from her mother over their political views. She marched in protests for racial justice to her mother’s outspoken disapproval, she said. All the while her mother, a longtime Democrat, became ever more supportive of President Trump.

headline.main: She saw her mother at the Capitol melee and called her out — publicly.

docs.abstract: Marcia Sells has been brought on to rethink equity and inclusion at the largest performing arts institution in the United States.
docs.snippet: Marcia Sells has been brought on to rethink equity and inclusion at the largest performing arts institution in the United States.
docs.lead_paragraph: Marcia Sells — a former dancer who became an assistant district attorney in Brooklyn and the dean of students at Harvard Law School — has been hired as the first chief diversity officer of the Metropolitan Opera, the largest performing arts institution in the United States.

headline.main: The Metropolitan Opera Hires Its First Chief Diversity Officer
headline.print_headline: Metropolitan Opera Hires First Chief Diversity Officer

docs.abstract: Loeffler, who co-owns the Atlanta Dream, lost her Senate race on Tuesday, renewing questions about whether she has a place in a league where many players want her gone.
docs.snippet: Loeffler, who co-owns the Atlanta Dream, lost her Senate race on Tuesday, renewing questions about whether she has a place in a league where many players want her gone.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Tuesday morning, the Rev. Raphael Warnock made a final pitch to Senate-race voters in Georgia with a video on social media that prominently featured W.N.B.A. players campaigning on his behalf against the Republican incumbent, Senator Kelly Loeffler, who also happens to be a co-owner of a franchise, the Atlanta Dream.

headline.main: Kelly Loeffler Is Done in the Senate. But What About in the W.N.B.A.?
headline.print_headline: Exploring What’s Next for Loeffler and the W.N.B.A.

docs.abstract: Teenage comments in response to our recent writing prompts, and an invitation to join the ongoing conversation.
docs.snippet: Teenage comments in response to our recent writing prompts, and an invitation to join the ongoing conversation.
docs.lead_paragraph: Welcome to another roundup of student comments on our writing prompts. This week we asked teenagers if they were concerned about soaring screen time during the pandemic, what they would do if they were president, and what fashion statements they’d like to make if money were no object.

headline.main: What Students Are Saying About Excessive Screen Time, Presidential Priorities and Fashion Statements

docs.abstract: Training and advancement as a chef can be hard to find in American fine-dining restaurants, according to Black women who have tried.
docs.snippet: Training and advancement as a chef can be hard to find in American fine-dining restaurants, according to Black women who have tried.
docs.lead_paragraph: Eight years ago, Auzerais Bellamy landed what she thought was a big break: a stint as a stagiaire, or apprentice, at the French Laundry, Thomas Keller’s world-renowned restaurant in the Napa Valley. She wasn’t paid for her two days trailing the pastry team, but she saw it as an ideal training ground where, if asked to stay, she could learn from some of the best cooks in the business, sharpening her skills.

headline.main: How High-End Restaurants Have Failed Black Female Chefs
headline.print_headline: Black Female Chefs Struggle to Move Up
